        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-13T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-13T16:00:00-05:00" n="1374" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1374">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">195.91/9–949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Macdonald</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-13T17:00:00-04:00">September 13, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>308. Re telCan 661 Sept 9, rptd Taipei 300, Nanking 1078, Shanghai 1839. As of
                    possible value expediting decision this question by Nat Govt authorities pls
                    bring attn Chen Cheng<note n="58" xml:id="d1374fn58">Governor of Taiwan
                        (Formosa).</note> situation outlined ref and previous tels, together with
                    APL counter-proposal and our view thereof. Stress strong demand Amers for
                    evacuation and fact that US Govt personnel being brought out as result reduction
                    offices Commie-held China. Within ur discretion also approach K. C. Wu<note n="59" xml:id="d1374fn59">Former Mayor of Shanghai.</note> along foregoing
                    lines, in view possibility he may be able reach ear of Gimo.<note n="60" xml:id="d1374fn60">Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek, with headquarters on
                        Taiwan.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
